As always, you can find the latest on our COVID-19 data page here and follow @nvindycovidbot for more!

https://t.co/h8eifMhX5o

Have questions about COVID-19, vaccines or the pandemic? Please submit them here so we can try and get them answered by experts!

https://t.co/Eqyhz25feM

Latest vaccine numbers from the CDC (same as yesterday):

💉 Total vaccine doses given: 4,714,873
1️⃣ Total given at least 1 dose: 2,281,093
2️⃣ Total fully vaccinated: 1,839,899
👥74.05% of Nevadans are fully or partially vaccinated
😷22.18% of Nevadans have received the booster https://t.co/L0StpYJjno

Updated wastewater sampling information from @SNWA_H2O shows decreased concentrations from sites in Clark County and Henderson and increased concentrations from sites in Las Vegas, North Las Vegas and Boulder City https://t.co/ahrBhNeATN

Clark vs. Washoe breakdowns:

🎰 Clark County cases are barely up: 638 (+7)
🏔 Washoe County cases are slightly up: 111 (+15) https://t.co/7or88D1ShM
